A photo posted by Miami Red Square Holdings (@miamiredsquareofficial) on Aug 2, 2016 at 10:34am PDT

Florida is a state in denial. Miami is in the midst of one of the largest building booms in the region's history. Dense crane canopies pepper the city's skyline as they soar over forthcoming white, gold, and aqua clad "high end" residential and hotel towers. This massive stream of investment dollars is downright paradoxical
